[[File:Shrivardhan Fort.(sunday 19-9-2010)..JPG|thumb|Shrivardhan fort]]
'''Shrivardhan fort''' is one of the two hill forts that constitute the Rajmachi fortification, the other being [[Manaranjan fort]].<ref name="fof">{{cite web|url=http://www.fortsofsahyadri.friendsofforts.com/list_of_maharashtraforts.htm|title=Friends of Forts|accessdate=2009-03-16}}</ref> It is located in [[Rajmachi]] village which 8.5&nbsp;km from [[Lonavala]] in the [[Sahyadris]] mountain range. At 900 m(3000 feet) above sea level it was the taller of the two peaks. Other than a rampart there is no visible construction. Probably it was used at a watchtower for the Sahyadri region. There are two water tanks at the top of the hill but one of them has an iron pillar in it. <ref name="gunaji">{{cite book|last=Gunaji|first=Milind|title=Offbeat Tracks in Maharashtra|publisher=Popular Prakashan|date=2005|pages=38â€“39|isbn=81-7154-669-2|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=JIjmDLardesC&pg=PA41&dq=raigad+fort&lr=|accessdate=2009-03-17}}</ref>

